<subSubSection id="87D697C32C55FFAAFCA053973AD5FD32" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CF73C4482C55FFAAFCA053973AD5FD32" blockId="13.[818,1444,449,733]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis id="FDB8185A2C55FFAAFCA053973D2EFE45" box="[818,878,450,468]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Notes:</emphasis>
We here propose the new genus 
<taxonomicName id="08CCBFCB2C55FFAAFB3D53943ABEFE44" authorityName="Camacho and Feitosa" authorityYear="2022" box="[1199,1278,449,469]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Boltonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FDB8185A2C55FFAAFB3D53943ABEFE44" box="[1199,1278,449,469]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Boltonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to accommodate a single species, 
<taxonomicName id="08CCBFCB2C55FFAAFC5F53B53AA0FE62" authority="(Borgmeier 1957)" authorityName="Camacho &amp; Franco &amp; Branstetter &amp; Pie &amp; Longino &amp; Schultz &amp; Feitosa" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Camacho &amp; Franco &amp; Branstetter &amp; Pie &amp; Longino &amp; Schultz &amp; Feitosa" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[973,1248,479,499]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Boltonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microps">
<emphasis id="FDB8185A2C55FFAAFC5F53B53A72FE63" box="[973,1074,480,498]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">B. microps</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AB5DB9B92C55FFAAFBD0538A3A98FE62" author="Borgmeier, T." box="[1090,1240,479,499]" journalOrPublisher="An. Acad. Bras. Cienc." pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="103 - 128" part="29" refId="ref17469" refString="Borgmeier, T. 1957. Myrmecologische Studien. An. Acad. Bras. Cienc. 29: 103 - 128." title="Myrmecologische Studien" type="journal article" year="1957">Borgmeier 1957</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, formerly a member of 
<taxonomicName id="08CCBFCB2C55FFAAFCDF53A83D8CFD9E" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1887" box="[845,972,509,527]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Heteroponera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FDB8185A2C55FFAAFCDF53A83D8CFD9E" box="[845,972,509,527]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Heteroponera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species represents a divergent lineage at the base of 
<taxonomicName id="08CCBFCB2C55FFAAFCEE504C3A49FDBC" authorityName="Bolton" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Camacho &amp; Franco &amp; Branstetter &amp; Pie &amp; Longino &amp; Schultz &amp; Feitosa" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[892,1033,537,557]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Heteroponerini">Heteroponerini</taxonomicName>
and is the sister-group of all the remaining species in the tribe. The genus name is an homage to Barry Bolton, legendary ant taxonomist and author of Boltonâ€™s Catalogue of Ants of the World, which is the very foundation of all taxonomic papers published in myrmecology since 1994.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
